text: uh hey everyone big thingy trem Tano
here the internet's busiest music nerd
and it's time for a review of this new
Thai boy digital album back to life this
is the newest full-length LP from Thai
rapper singer songwriter tyboy digital
it's been a minute since his legendary
member record in 2019 also the collab
album he put out with a blade and Echo
2K that same year so I was curious to
see if in that time tyboy had come up
with anything new exciting refreshing
maybe even reaching a new level of
refinement artistically but I gotta say
the Aesthetics and style of this project
are pretty much part of the course for
everything we've heard from Thai boy and
drain gang generally so far which is a
bit odd considering blade and Echo 2K
are pretty handily pushing the
boundaries of their sound with every
project and I think tyboy's choice to
play it safe on this one has led to a
lack of excitement as well as
intoxicating Bliss the intro cut dream
world doesn't exactly set the album up
to be intriguing maybe decent but not
intriguing the synthy trap beat in my
opinion is sort of dry by drain gang
standards back to life just feels so
much more average texturally even as
Thai boy's Reverb soaked falsettos call
out into the nothing on the back end of
the title track though I do find his own
personal story of persevering and
sticking to his art for so long to be
inspiring there's also a matter of his
very emotionally flat boyish auto-tune
soaked vocals and wraps which yes are
pretty much a tie boy in drain gang
trademark at this point definitely an
acquired taste and one I'm not always in
the mood for with it coming across as
one-dimensional as it does usually I
need some stand-up songwriting or
production to kind of close the
enjoyability gap but a lot of tracks on
this LP just don't have that not just
because they're average by Ty boys
standards but I would say below average
at some points like with the lyrics on
Angel only one kiss I enter the Bliss
only York lips I want to kiss really
this album's best moments are the ones
where it's chorus writing is at its
sharpest be that on the song Live keep
my fans close my enemies closer the
performance on this track is definitely
stand out as well with Ty boys sounding
more chipper here than he has on any cut
so far because the blade and young lean
crossover earlier on the lp wasn't
exactly fireworks there's also something
really cute and moving about the devoted
and lovesick fate the spacious mix the
Warped whistling synth leads as well as
tyboy's melodic bars saying things like
ain't no way in hell I'm Gonna Let You
Down on this road alone and the
structure of the cup makes it super
catchy despite the delivery being so
low-key true love sees young lean back
in the mix with some much more lively
production from Rock the bright and
burning synthesizers on this one are
fantastic they may not be the wintry
trademark that we expect from most drain
gang stuff but I kind of prefer this
Vibe over many of the more toothless
moments on the lp and then it's sort of
like the album wakes up a little bit
past this point the kingdom is a banger
in terms of its volume and punchiness
blade may carry a majority of the track
yes and maybe the track smacks of being
a bit redundant shoulder to shoulder
with another cut that features blade a
better one in fact but still the song is
more exciting than anything going on on
the first leg of the album three star we
unite 3 star reunite is that better
track that I was just referring to that
one goes off as well and Mr CEO is a
pretty smooth earworm as well so yeah
there's most definitely some great
highlights on this thing but at the same
time there's a lot of lost potential too
be it on a very one-dimensional track a
very short and half big track like in
the case of Love Potion whose Grand
synth leads on the intro are fantastic
and really set the song up to be an
Anthem but from there it never really
reaches another high point then never
change the closing track is kind of a
sweet little meditation over the most
sparse and skeletal beat on the entire
LP there are a few lovely keyboard
resolutions the vocals sound pretty a
vast majority of the time but none of
these sweet sounds are carried by a
super compelling song or anything like
that and as a result I think Ty boys
evocative images of rivers and moons and
clouds don't have the impact they could
so overall I felt like this LP was just
kind of okay again had some highlights
uh brought that classic drain gang sound
but didn't do anything beyond that to
really stand out which considering the
amount of hype and attention this style
of music is getting right now I think
tyboy could have pulled out the big guns
a little bit more feeling a light to
decent six on this one transition have
